msgid "Line"
msgstr "Linija"

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:448
msgid "Use ``:numref:`` roles to reference tables like this:"
msgstr "Koristite uloge ``:numref:`` za upućivanje na tabele ovako:"

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:456
msgid "see :numref:`table-grid-caption` or :numref:`table-list-caption`"
msgstr ""
"pogledajte :numref:`table-grid-caption` ili :numref:`table-list-caption`"

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:460
msgid ""
"You must add a caption to your table in order to create a cross reference "
"with the ``:numref:`` role."
msgstr ""
"Morate dodati natpis svojoj tabeli da biste napravili unakrsnu referencu "
"pomoću uloge ``:numref:``."

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:464
msgid "Index"
msgstr "Index"

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:466
msgid ""
"An index is a handy way to help the reader find information in a document. "
"QGIS documentation provides some essential indices. There are a few rules "
"that help us provide a set of indices that are really useful (coherent, "
"consistent and really connected to each other):"
msgstr ""
"Indeks je zgodan način da se čitaocu pomogne da pronađe informacije u "
"dokumentu. QGIS dokumentacija pruža neke suštinske indekse. Postoji nekoliko"
" pravila koja nam pomažu da pružimo skup indeksa koji su zaista korisni "
"(koherentni, dosledni i zaista međusobno povezani):"

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:471
msgid ""
"An index should be human readable, understandable and translatable; an index"
" can be made from many words but you should avoid any unneeded ``_``, "
"``-``... characters to link them i.e., ``Loading layers`` instead of "
"``loading_layers`` or ``loadingLayers``."
msgstr ""
"Indeks treba da bude čitljiv, razumljiv i prevodiv; indeks se može sastojati"
" od više reči, ali treba da izbegavate sve nepotrebne znakove ``_``, "
"``-``... za njihovo povezivanje, tj. ``Loading layers`` umesto "
"``loading_layers`` ili ``loadingLayers``."

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:475
msgid ""
"Capitalize only the first letter of the index unless the word has a "
"particular spelling. E.g., ``Loading layers``, ``Atlas generation``, "
"``WMS``, ``pgsql2shp``."
msgstr ""
"Velikim slovom pišite samo prvo slovo indeksa, osim ako reč ima poseban "
"način pisanja. Npr. ``Loading layers``, ``Atlas generation``, ``WMS``, "
"``pgsql2shp``."

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:478
msgid ""
"Keep an eye on the existing `Index list "
"<https://docs.qgis.org/testing/en/genindex.html>`_ in order to reuse the "
"most convenient expression with the right spelling and avoid unnecessary "
"duplicates."
msgstr ""
"Obratite pažnju na postojeću `listu indeksa "
"<https://docs.qgis.org/testing/en/genindex.html>`_ da biste ponovo "
"iskoristili najpogodniji izraz sa ispravnim pisanjem i izbegli nepotrebne "
"duplikate."

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:482
msgid ""
"Several index tags exist in reST. You can use the inline ``:index:`` tag "
"within normal text:"
msgstr ""
"U reST-u postoji nekoliko oznaka indeksa. Možete koristiti ugrađenu oznaku "
"``:index:`` unutar običnog teksta:"

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:489
msgid ""
"Or you can use the ``.. index::`` block-level markup which links to the "
"beginning of the next paragraph. Because of the rules mentioned above, it is"
" recommended to use the block-level tag:"
msgstr ""
"Ili možete koristiti markup na nivou bloka ``.. index::`` koji vodi ka "
"početku sledećeg pasusa. Zbog gore pomenutih pravila, preporučuje se "
"korišćenje oznake na nivou bloka:"

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:497
msgid ""
"It is also recommended to use index parameters such as ``single``, ``pair`` "
"and ``see``, in order to build a more structured and interconnected index "
"table. See `Index generating <https://www.sphinx-"
"doc.org/en/master/usage/restructuredtext/directives.html#index-generating-"
"markup>`_ for more information on index creation."
msgstr ""
"Takođe se preporučuje korišćenje parametara indeksa kao što su ``single``, "
"``pair`` i ``see``, radi izgradnje strukturiranije i međusobno povezane "
"tabele indeksa. Za više informacija o pravljenju indeksa pogledajte "
"`Generisanje indeksa <https://www.sphinx-"
"doc.org/en/master/usage/restructuredtext/directives.html#index-generating-"
"markup>`_."

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:504
msgid "Special Comments"
msgstr "Specijalni komentari"

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:506
msgid ""
"Sometimes, you may want to emphasize some points of the description, either "
"to warn, remind or give some hints to the user. In QGIS Documentation, we "
"use reST special directives such as ``.. warning::``, ``.. seealso::``, ``.."
" note::`` and ``.. tip::``. These directives generate frames that highlight "
"your comments. See `Paragraph Level markup <https://www.sphinx-"
"doc.org/en/master/usage/restructuredtext/directives.html#paragraph-level-"
"markup>`_ for more information. A clear and appropriate title is required "
"for both warnings and tips."
msgstr ""
"Ponekad ćete možda želeti da istaknete neke tačke opisa, bilo da upozorite, "
"podsetite ili date neke savete korisniku. U QGIS dokumentaciji koristimo "
"reST specijalne direktive kao što su ``.. warning::``, ``.. seealso::``, "
"``.. note::`` i ``.. tip::``. Ove direktive generišu okvire koji ističu vaše"
" komentare. Za više informacija pogledajte `Markup na nivou pasusa "
"<https://www.sphinx-"
"doc.org/en/master/usage/restructuredtext/directives.html#paragraph-level-"
"markup>`_. Jasan i odgovarajući naslov je obavezan i za upozorenja i za "
"savete."

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:524
msgid "Code Snippets"
msgstr "Isečci koda"

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:526
msgid ""
"You may also want to give examples and insert code snippets. In this case, "
"write the comment below a line with the ``::`` directive inserted.  For a "
"better rendering, especially to apply color highlighting to code according "
"to its language, use the code-block directive, e.g. ``.. code-block:: xml``."
" More details at `Showing code <https://www.sphinx-"
"doc.org/en/master/usage/restructuredtext/directives.html#showing-code-"
"examples>`_."
msgstr ""
"Možda ćete takođe želeti da date primere i umetnete isečke koda. U tom "
"slučaju napišite komentar ispod reda sa umetnutom direktivom ``::``. Za "
"bolje iscrtavanje, naročito za primenu isticanja boja na kôd prema njegovom "
"jeziku, koristite direktivu code-block, npr. ``.. code-block:: xml``. Više "
"detalja na `Prikaz koda <https://www.sphinx-"
"doc.org/en/master/usage/restructuredtext/directives.html#showing-code-"
"examples>`_."

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:535
msgid ""
"Text in special comments will be translated, but text in code-block frames "
"will not be translated. So keep comments in code blocks as short as possible"
" and avoid comments unrelated to code."
msgstr ""
"Tekst u specijalnim komentarima biće preveden, ali tekst u okvirima code-"
"block neće biti preveden. Zato držite komentare u blokovima koda što je "
"kraće moguće i izbegavajte komentare nepovezane sa kodom."

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:541
msgid "Footnotes"
msgstr "Fusnote"

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:544
msgid "This is for creating a footnote (showing as example [1]_)"
msgstr "Ovo je za pravljenje fusnote (prikazuje se kao primer [1]_)"

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:550
msgid "Which will point to:"
msgstr "Što će voditi ka:"

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:552
msgid "Updates of core plugins"
msgstr "Ažuriranja osnovnih dodataka"

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:557
msgid "Managing Screenshots"
msgstr "Upravljanje snimcima ekrana"

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:560
msgid "Add new Screenshots"
msgstr "Dodavanje novih snimaka ekrana"

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:562
msgid ""
"Here are some hints to create new, nice looking screenshots. The images "
"should be placed in an image (:file:`img/`) folder that is located in the "
"same folder as the referencing :file:`.rst` file."
msgstr ""
"Evo nekih saveta za pravljenje novih, lepih snimaka ekrana. Slike treba "
"postaviti u folder slika (:file:`img/`) koji se nalazi u istom folderu kao "
":file:`.rst` datoteka koja ih referencira."

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:566
msgid ""
"You can find some prepared QGIS projects that are used to create screenshots"
" in the :file:`./qgis-projects` folder of this repository. This makes it "
"easier to reproduce screenshots for the next version of QGIS. These projects"
" use the QGIS `Sample Data <https://github.com/qgis/QGIS-Sample-"
"Data/archive/master.zip>`_ (aka Alaska Dataset), which should be unzipped "
"and placed in the same folder as the QGIS-Documentation Repository."
msgstr ""
"Neke pripremljene QGIS projekte koji se koriste za pravljenje snimaka ekrana"
" možete pronaći u folderu :file:`./qgis-projects` ovog repozitorijuma. Time "
"se olakšava reprodukcija snimaka ekrana za sledeću verziju QGIS-a. Ovi "
"projekti koriste QGIS `uzorne podatke <https://github.com/qgis/QGIS-Sample-"
"Data/archive/master.zip>`_ (poznate i kao Alaska skup podataka), koje treba "
"raspakovati i postaviti u isti folder kao repozitorijum QGIS-Documentation."

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:572
msgid ""
"Reduce the window to the minimal space needed to show the feature (taking "
"the whole screen for a small modal window > overkill)"
msgstr ""
"Smanjite prozor na minimalni prostor potreban za prikaz mogućnosti (uzimanje"
" celog ekrana za mali modalni prozor > preterivanje)"

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:574
msgid "The less clutter, the better (no need to activate all the toolbars)"
msgstr ""
"Što manje zbrke, to bolje (nema potrebe za aktiviranjem svih paleta alatki)"

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:575
msgid ""
"Don't resize them in an image editor; the size will be set into the "
":file:`.rst` files if necessary (downscaling the dimensions without properly"
" upping the resolution > ugly)"
msgstr ""
"Nemojte im menjati veličinu u uređivaču slika; veličina će biti postavljena "
"u :file:`.rst` datotekama ako je potrebno (smanjivanje dimenzija bez "
"propisnog povećanja rezolucije > ružno)"

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:578
msgid "Cut the background"
msgstr "Isecite pozadinu"

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:579
msgid "Make the top corners transparent if the background is not white"
msgstr "Učinite gornje uglove prozirnim ako pozadina nije bela"

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:580
msgid ""
"Set print size resolution to ``135 dpi`` (e.g., in GIMP scale down the image"
" using :menuselection:`Image --> Scale Image` and setting \"X/Y\" to ``135 "
"pixels/in``, and export it through :menuselection:`File --> Export...`). "
"This way, images will be at original size in HTML and at a good print "
"resolution in the PDF."
msgstr ""
"Postavite rezoluciju veličine štampe na ``135 dpi`` (npr. u GIMP-u smanjite "
"sliku pomoću :menuselection:`Image --> Scale Image` i postavljanjem „X/Y“ na"
" ``135 pixels/in``, i izvezite je kroz :menuselection:`File --> Export...`)."
" Na ovaj način, slike će biti u originalnoj veličini u HTML-u i u dobroj "
"rezoluciji štampe u PDF-u."

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:586
msgid "You can also use ImageMagick convert command to do a batch of images:"
msgstr "Za paket slika možete koristiti i ImageMagick convert komandu:"

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:592
msgid "Save them as :file:`.png` (to avoid :file:`.jpeg` artifacts)"
msgstr ""
"Sačuvajte ih kao :file:`.png` (da biste izbegli :file:`.jpeg` artefakte)"

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:593
msgid ""
"The screenshot should show the content according to what is described in the"
" text"
msgstr ""
"Snimak ekrana treba da prikazuje sadržaj u skladu sa onim što je opisano u "
"tekstu"

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:596
msgid ""
"If you are on Ubuntu, you can use the following command to remove the global"
" menu function and create smaller application screens with menus:"
msgstr ""
"Ako ste na Ubuntu-u, možete koristiti sledeću komandu da uklonite funkciju "
"globalnog menija i napravite manje ekrane aplikacije sa menijima:"

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:605
msgid "Translated Screenshots"
msgstr "Prevedeni snimci ekrana"

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:607
msgid ""
"Here are some additional hints for those that want to create screenshots for"
" a translated user guide:"
msgstr ""
"Evo nekih dodatnih saveta za one koji žele da naprave snimke ekrana za "
"prevedeni korisnički vodič:"

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:610
msgid ""
"Translated images should be placed in a :file:`img/<your_language>/` folder."
" Use the same filename as the 'original' English screenshot."
msgstr ""
"Prevedene slike treba postaviti u folder :file:`img/<your_language>/`. "
"Koristite isti naziv datoteke kao „originalni“ engleski snimak ekrana."

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:615
msgid "Documenting Processing algorithms"
msgstr "Dokumentovanje algoritama obrade"

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:617
msgid ""
"If you want to write documentation for Processing algorithms, consider these"
" guidelines:"
msgstr ""
"Ako želite da pišete dokumentaciju za algoritme obrade, razmotrite ove "
"smernice:"

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:620
msgid ""
"Processing algorithm help files are part of QGIS User Guide, so use the same"
" formatting as the User Guide and other documentation."
msgstr ""
"Datoteke pomoći algoritama obrade su deo QGIS korisničkog vodiča, pa "
"koristite isto formatiranje kao korisnički vodič i druga dokumentacija."

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:623
msgid ""
"Each algorithm documentation should be placed in the corresponding "
"**provider** folder and **group** file, e.g. the algorithm `Voronoi polygon`"
" belongs to the `QGIS` provider and to the group `vectorgeometry`. So the "
"correct file to add the description is: "
":file:`source/docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst`."
msgstr ""
"Dokumentacija svakog algoritma treba da bude postavljena u odgovarajući "
"folder **provajdera** i datoteku **grupe**, npr. algoritam `Voronoi polygon`"
" pripada `QGIS` provajderu i grupi `vectorgeometry`. Dakle, ispravna "
"datoteka za dodavanje opisa je: "
":file:`source/docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst`."

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:628
msgid ""
"Before starting to write the guide, check if the algorithm is already "
"described. In this case, you can enhance the existing description."
msgstr ""
"Pre nego što počnete da pišete vodič, proverite da li je algoritam već "
"opisan. U tom slučaju možete poboljšati postojeći opis."

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:631
msgid ""
"It is **extremely** important that each algorithm has an *anchor* that "
"corresponds to the provider name + the unique name of the algorithm itself. "
"This allows the Help button to open the Help page of the correct section. "
"The anchor should be placed **above** the title, e.g. (see also the "
":ref:`my_anchor` section):"
msgstr ""
"**Izuzetno** je važno da svaki algoritam ima *sidro* koje odgovara nazivu "
"provajdera + jedinstvenom nazivu samog algoritma. Time se dugmetu Pomoć "
"omogućava da otvori stranicu Pomoć ispravnog odeljka. Sidro treba postaviti "
"**iznad** naslova, npr. (pogledajte i odeljak :ref:`my_anchor`):"

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:643
msgid ""
"To find out the algorithm name you can just hover the mouse on the algorithm"
" in the Processing toolbox."
msgstr ""
"Da biste saznali naziv algoritma, samo zadržite pokazivač miša iznad "
"algoritma u kutiji sa alatkama za obradu."

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:645
msgid "Mention the QGIS version in which the algorithm was introduced:"
msgstr "Pomenite QGIS verziju u kojoj je algoritam uveden:"

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:651
msgid ""
"Likewise, mention if the algorithm requires a specific optional dependency "
"(and version)."
msgstr ""
"Isto tako, pomenite ako algoritam zahteva određenu opcionu zavisnost (i "
"verziju)."

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:658
msgid ""
"Avoid using \"This algorithm does this and that...\" as the first sentence "
"in the algorithm description. Try to use more general expressions like:"
msgstr ""
"Izbegavajte korišćenje „Ovaj algoritam radi to i to...“ kao prve rečenice u "
"opisu algoritma. Pokušajte da koristite opštije izraze kao što su:"

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:665
msgid ""
"Avoid describing what the algorithm does by replicating its name and please "
"don't replicate the name of the parameter in the description of the "
"parameter itself. For example if the algorithm is ``Voronoi polygon`` "
"consider to describe the ``Input layer`` as ``Layer to calculate the polygon"
" from``."
msgstr ""
"Izbegavajte opisivanje onoga što algoritam radi ponavljanjem njegovog naziva"
" i nemojte ponavljati naziv parametra u opisu samog parametra. Na primer, "
"ako je algoritam ``Voronoi polygon``, razmotrite da opišete ``Input layer`` "
"kao ``Sloj iz kojeg se računa poligon``."

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:669
msgid ""
"Indicate in the description whether the algorithm has a default shortcut in "
"QGIS or supports in-place editing."
msgstr ""
"U opisu navedite da li algoritam ima podrazumevanu prečicu u QGIS-u ili "
"podržava izmenu na licu mesta."

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:671
msgid ""
"Add images! A picture is worth a thousand words! Use :file:`.png` format and"
" follow the general guidelines for documentation (see the :ref:`image` "
"section for more info). Put the image file in the correct folder, i.e. the "
":file:`img` folder next to the :file:`.rst` file you are editing."
msgstr ""
"Dodajte slike! Slika vredi hiljadu reči! Koristite :file:`.png` format i "
"pratite opšte smernice za dokumentaciju (za više informacija pogledajte "
"odeljak :ref:`image`). Stavite datoteku slike u ispravan folder, tj. folder "
":file:`img` pored :file:`.rst` datoteke koju menjate."

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:675
msgid ""
"If necessary, add links in the \"See also\" section that provide additional "
"information about the algorithm  (e.g., publications or web-pages).  Only "
"add the \"See also\" section if there is really something to see. As a good "
"practice, the \"See also\" section can be filled with links to similar "
"algorithms."
msgstr ""
"Ako je potrebno, dodajte linkove u odeljak „Pogledajte i“ koji pružaju "
"dodatne informacije o algoritmu (npr. publikacije ili veb stranice). Dodajte"
" odeljak „Pogledajte i“ samo ako zaista ima šta da se vidi. Kao dobra "
"praksa, odeljak „Pogledajte i“ može se popuniti linkovima ka sličnim "
"algoritmima."

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:679
msgid ""
"Give clear explanation for algorithm parameters and outputs: take "
"inspiration from existing algorithms."
msgstr ""
"Dajte jasno objašnjenje za parametre i izlaze algoritma: inspirišite se "
"postojećim algoritmima."

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:681
msgid ""
"Avoid duplicating detailed description of algorithm options. Add this "
"information in the parameter description."
msgstr ""
"Izbegavajte dupliranje detaljnog opisa opcija algoritma. Dodajte ovu "
"informaciju u opis parametra."

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:683
msgid ""
"Avoid adding information about the vector geometry type in the algorithm or "
"parameter description, as this information is already available in the "
"parameter descriptions."
msgstr ""
"Izbegavajte dodavanje informacija o tipu vektorske geometrije u opis "
"algoritma ili parametra, pošto je ova informacija već dostupna u opisima "
"parametara."

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:685
msgid "Add the default value of the parameter, e.g.:"
msgstr "Dodajte podrazumevanu vrednost parametra, npr.:"

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:696
msgid ""
"When a parameter or a parameter's value is added to an already existing "
"algorithm, indicate the QGIS version in which it is introduced. If it "
"requires a specific library, also indicate its minimal requirements."
msgstr ""
"Kada se parametar ili vrednost parametra doda već postojećem algoritmu, "
"navedite QGIS verziju u kojoj je uveden. Ako zahteva određenu biblioteku, "
"navedite i njene minimalne zahteve."

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:699
msgid ""
"Describe the *type* of input supported the parameters. There are several "
"types available you can pick one from:"
msgstr ""
"Opišite *tip* ulaza koji parametri podržavaju. Dostupno je nekoliko tipova, "
"možete izabrati jedan od:"

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:703
msgid "Parameter/Output type"
msgstr "Tip parametra/izlaza"

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:703
msgid "Visual indicator"
msgstr "Vizuelni pokazatelj"

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:705
msgid "Point vector layer"
msgstr "Tačkasti vektorski sloj"

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:705
msgid "``vector: point``"
msgstr "``vector: point``"

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:705
msgid "|pointLayer|"
msgstr "|pointLayer|"

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:873
msgid "pointLayer"
msgstr "pointLayer"

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:706
msgid "Line vector layer"
msgstr "Linijski vektorski sloj"

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:706
msgid "``vector: line``"
msgstr "``vector: line``"

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:706
msgid "|lineLayer|"
msgstr "|lineLayer|"

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:865
msgid "lineLayer"
msgstr "lineLayer"

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:707
msgid "Polygon vector layer"
msgstr "Poligonski vektorski sloj"

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:707
msgid "``vector: polygon``"
msgstr "``vector: polygon``"

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:707
msgid "|polygonLayer|"
msgstr "|polygonLayer|"

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:875
msgid "polygonLayer"
msgstr "polygonLayer"

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:708
msgid "All spatial vector layers"
msgstr "Svi prostorni vektorski slojevi"

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:708
msgid "``vector: geometry``"
msgstr "``vector: geometry``"

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:709
msgid "Geometryless vector layer"
msgstr "Vektorski sloj bez geometrije"

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:709
msgid "``vector: table``"
msgstr "``vector: table``"

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:709
msgid "|tableLayer|"
msgstr "|tableLayer|"

#: ../../docs/documentation_guidelines/writing.rst:885
